title: North Macedonia Manufacturing Production
description: Manufacturing Production in Macedonia increased 5.40 percent in September of 2022 over the same month in the previous year. Manufacturing Production in Macedonia averaged 2.03 percent from 2001 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 64.40 percent in April of 2021 and a record low of -40.60 percent in April of 2020. This page provides - Macedonia Manufacturing Production - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: EUROSTAT
